<DOC><DOCNO> SJMN91-06318176 </DOCNO><ACCESS> 06318176 </ACCESS><DESCRIPT>  MORGAN-HILL; AVIATION; ACCIDENT; VICTIM; MEXICO  </DESCRIPT><LEADPARA>  Three Morgan Hill residents and a Sacramento woman were killed Saturday whentheir private plane stalled and crashed near a seashore hotel in BajaCalifornia.;   The victims were Bill Bond, 56, his son Devin, 24, and NormaJune Maddock, 34, all of Morgan Hill, and Holly Rene Christie, 30, ofSacramento.  </LEADPARA><SECTION>  Local  </SECTION><HEADLINE>  3 M.H. RESIDENTS DIE WHEN PLANE CRASHES IN BAJACALIFORNIA  </HEADLINE><TEXT>     Bill Bond, flying a four-place Beechcraft Bonanza, was pulling up aftermaking a low pass in front of the hotel when the plane stalled.;   Thevictims, members of the Morgan Hill Airmen's Association, were among 10present or former residents of the area who were spending the weekend at theHotel Punta Chivato on the Sea of Cortes, said Barbara Schwab of San Martin.;  The hotel is about 10 miles north of Mulege, a town of 7,000 about 650 milessouth of the border.;   Schwab said her husband, Paul, and Bond decided aboutnoon Saturday to fly to Loreto, 60 miles south of the hotel, to fuel theirplanes, eat lunch and shop. The other four members of the party, who hadarrived in a third plane, were not going, she said.;   Schwab said she and herhusband were getting into their plane when Bond, who had already taken off,made a low pass in front of the hotel, a tradition with many pilots.;   &quot;Notall the pilots did it, but it was a custom with many of them,&quot; Schwab said.;  Bond was trying to gain altitude when his plane stalled, Schwab said. Thecraft came straight down, nose first. It hit a low ridge and came to rest onthe beach.;   Bill Bond owned Valley Financial Services in Gilroy. Devin Bondwas studying business at California State University, Sacramento, andChristie, who lived in Hollister at one time, was a senior nursing student atthe same university.;   Bill Bond had organized many tours for members of theflying group, Schwab said.;   She said funeral arrangements are pending.;  The Bond party had left South County Airport in San Martin.  </TEXT><BYLINE>  DALE RODEBAUGH, Mercury News Staff Writer  </BYLINE><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><EDITION>  South County  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  </CODE><NAME>  San Jose Mercury News  </NAME><PUBDATE>   911113  </PUBDATE> <DAY>  Wednesday  </DAY><MONTH>  November  </MONTH><PG.COL>  1B  </PG.COL><PUBYEAR>  1991  </PUBYEAR><REGION>  WEST  </REGION><STATE>  CA  </STATE><WORD.CT>  331  </WORD.CT><DATELINE>  Wednesday, November 13, 199100318176,SJ1  </DATELINE><COPYRGHT>  Copyright 1991, San Jose Mercury News  </COPYRGHT><LIMLEN>  1  </LIMLEN><LANGUAGE>  ENG  </LANGUAGE></DOC>